member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVACalcObjectElem.eVACalcObjectElemBrouwerLyddaneMeanLong
member.summary: Brouwer-Lyddane mean elements considering both the short and long period terms (i.e. resulting from averaging over the rotation of periapse). The perturbation terms are the J2, J3, J4 and J5 oblateness terms and it considers the term involving J2^2.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVACalcObjectElem.eVACalcObjectElemBrouwerLyddaneMeanShort
member.summary: Brouwer-Lyddane Mean Short - Brouwer-Lyddane mean elements considering only the short period terms (i.e. those involving averaging over the period of the orbit) where the only perturbation force is the oblateness arising from the J2 gravity term.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVACalcObjectElem.eVACalcObjectElemKozaiIzsakMean
member.summary: Kozai-Izsak Mean - Kozai-Izsak mean elements for which only the short period terms (i.e. those involving averaging over the period of the orbit) are considered. The only perturbation force considered is the oblateness arising from the J2 gravity term.

member.name: T:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAErrorControl
member.summary: Error Control for the numerical integrator.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAErrorControl.eVAErrorControlAbsolute
member.summary: The error estimate of each integrated component is compared to the absolute error tolerance. Error control with this method is based on absolute values, e.g. in meters for position, m/sec for velocity, etc.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAErrorControl.eVAErrorControlRelativeByComponent
member.summary: The error estimate of each element being integrated relative to the element's value at the start of the step is compared to the relative error tolerance, and the absolute error estimate of each element is compared to the absolute error tolerance.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAErrorControl.eVAErrorControlRelativeToState
member.summary: Relative to State error control.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAErrorControl.eVAErrorControlRelativeToStep
member.summary: Error estimate of each integrated component relative to the element's change in value over the step is compared to the relative error tolerance, and the absolute error estimate of each integrated component is compared to the absolute error tolerance.

member.summary: Predictor corrector scheme for the numerical integrator.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAPredictorCorrector.eVAPredictorCorrectorFull
member.summary: All force models are re-evaluated at each corrector step.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAPredictorCorrector.eVAPredictorCorrectorPseudo
member.summary: Only the two-body acceleration is re-evaluated at each corrector step.

member.name: T:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVANumericalIntegrator
member.summary: Numerical integrator type.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVANumericalIntegrator.eVANumericalIntegratorRK4thAdapt
member.summary: A 4th order Runge-Kutta integrator, adapting step size by comparing one full step to two half steps. Although this technique can be quite slow compared to the other algorithms, it is very common and can be used for comparison.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVANumericalIntegrator.eVANumericalIntegratorRKF7th8th
member.summary: A 7th order Runge-Kutta-Fehlberg integrator with 8th order error control. This is the default integrator used in the HPOP propagator.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVANumericalIntegrator.eVANumericalIntegratorRKV8th9th
member.summary: A 9th order Runge-Kutta-Verner integrator with 8th order error control.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVANumericalIntegrator.eVANumericalIntegratorBulirschStoer
member.summary: An integrator based on Richardson extrapolation with automatic step size control.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVANumericalIntegrator.eVANumericalIntegratorGaussJackson
member.summary: A 12th order Gauss-Jackson integrator for second order ODEs. There is currently no error control implemented for this method, meaning that a fixed step size is used.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVANumericalIntegrator.eVANumericalIntegratorRK2nd3rd
member.summary: A 2nd order Runge-Kutta integrator with 3rd order error control, using Bogacki and Shampine coefficients.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVANumericalIntegrator.eVANumericalIntegratorRK4th5th
member.summary: A 4th order Runge-Kutta integrator with 5th order error control, using Cash-Karp coefficients.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVANumericalIntegrator.eVANumericalIntegratorRK4th
member.summary: A 4th order Runge-Kutta integrator that does not employ error control.

member.summary: Initial State - can be used to define the initial conditions of your MCS, or of a subsequence within the MCS.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVASegmentType.eVASegmentTypeLaunch
member.summary: Launch - can be used to model a simple spacecraft launch from Earth or another central body.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVASegmentType.eVASegmentTypeManeuver
member.summary: Maneuver - can be used to model a spacecraft maneuver.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVASegmentType.eVASegmentTypeFollow
member.summary: Follow - can be used to set the spacecraft to follow another vehicle (Satellite, Launch Vehicle, Missile, Aircraft, Ship, or Ground Vehicle) at a specified offset, and to separate from that vehicle upon meeting specified conditions.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVASegmentType.eVASegmentTypeHold
member.summary: Hold - can be used to model landing or rendezvous operations by setting the spacecraft to maintain a fixed position in reference to another object or body, until meeting specified conditions.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVASegmentType.eVASegmentTypePropagate
member.summary: Propagate - can be used to model the movement of the spacecraft along its current trajectory until meeting specified stopping conditions.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVASegmentType.eVASegmentTypeSequence
member.summary: Sequence - can be used to organize segments and define the nature of the results that are passed on to the next segment or sequence in the MCS.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVASegmentType.eVASegmentTypeReturn
member.summary: Return - can be used to control the execution of the Mission Control Sequence by returning control to its parent segment.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVASegmentType.eVASegmentTypeTargetSequence
member.summary: Target Sequence - can be used to define maneuvers and propagations in terms of the goals they are intended to achieve.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVASegmentType.eVASegmentTypeStop
member.summary: Stop - can be used to control the execution of the Mission Control Sequence by halting execution of the MCS.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVASegmentType.eVASegmentTypeUpdate
member.summary: Update - can be used to modify some of the satellite properties to reflect changes that occur during the mission.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVASegmentType.eVASegmentTypeBackwardSequence
member.summary: Backward Sequence - can be used to organize segments and define the nature of the results that are passed on to the next segment or sequence in the MCS.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVASegmentType.eVASegmentTypeEnd
member.summary: End - The End segment is a default segment of the MCS that functions similarly to a Return segment; it returns control to the beginning of the MCS. The End segment cannot be disabled or deleted, nor can any segments be inserted into the MCS after it.

member.summary: Properties for spacecraft configuration.

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.IAgVASpacecraftParameters.DryMass
member.summary: The mass of the spacecraft exclusive of propellant. Uses Mass Dimension.

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.IAgVASpacecraftParameters.Cd
member.summary: The dimensionless drag coefficient associated with the drag area. Dimensionless.

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.IAgVASpacecraftParameters.DragArea
member.summary: The cross-sectional area of the spacecraft assumed perpendicular to the direction of motion, used for atmospheric drag calculations. Uses SmallArea Dimension.

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.IAgVASpacecraftParameters.Cr
member.summary: The reflectivity of the spacecraft used for solar radiation pressure calculations, where 2.0 is fully reflective and 1.0 is not reflective at all. Dimensionless.

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.IAgVASpacecraftParameters.SolarRadiationPressureArea
member.summary: The cross-sectional area of the spacecraft assumed perpendicular to the direction of solar radiation, used for solar radiation calculations. Uses SmallArea Dimension.

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.IAgVASpacecraftParameters.Ck
member.summary: The reflectivity of the spacecraft used for central body radiation pressure (albedo / thermal pressure) calculations, where 2.0 is fully reflective and 1.0 is not reflective at all. Dimensionless.

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.IAgVASpacecraftParameters.RadiationPressureArea
member.summary: The cross-sectional area of the spacecraft assumed perpendicular to the direction of central body radiation, used for central body radiation (albedo / thermal pressure) calculations. Uses SmallArea Dimension.

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.IAgVASpacecraftParameters.K1
member.summary: If you are using a non-spherical SRP model, this field defines the model's GPS solar radiation pressure K1 (scale) value. Dimensionless.

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.IAgVASpacecraftParameters.K2
member.summary: If you are using a non-spherical SRP model, this field defines the model's GPS solar radiation pressure K2 (scale) value. Dimensionless.

member.summary: Vz Component - the Z component of the spacecraft velocity vector.

member.summary: X Component - the X component of the spacecraft position vector.

member.summary: Y Component - the Y component of the spacecraft position vector.

member.summary: Z Component - the Z component of the spacecraft position vector.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateCd
member.summary: Drag Coefficient (Cd) - the dimensionless drag coefficient associated with the drag area.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateCr
member.summary: Solar Radiation Pressure (Spherical) Coefficient (Cr) - the reflectivity of the spacecraft used for solar radiation pressure calculations, where 2.0 is fully reflective and 1.0 is not reflective at all.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateDragArea
member.summary: Drag Area - the cross-sectional area of the spacecraft assumed perpendicular to the direction of motion, used for atmospheric drag calculations. Enter a value in the selected distance unit squared.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateDryMass
member.summary: Dry Mass - the mass of the spacecraft exclusive of propellant. Enter a value in the selected mass unit (e.g. kg).

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateEpoch
member.summary: Epoch - the orbit epoch.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateFuelDensity
member.summary: Fuel Density - the density of the fuel tank.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateK1
member.summary: GPS Solar Radiation Pressure K1 - if you are using a non-spherical SRP model, this field defines the model's K1 (scale) value.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateK2
member.summary: GPS Solar Radiation Pressure K2 - if you are using a non-spherical SRP model, this field defines the model's K2 (Y bias) value.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateKeplerianEcc
member.summary: Eccentricity - the ratio of the distance between the foci to the major axis of the orbital ellipse. Dimensionless.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateKeplerianInc
member.summary: Inclination - the angle from the +Z axis of the coordinate system to the angular momentum vector of the spacecraft's orbit.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateKeplerianRAAN
member.summary: Right Ascension of Ascending Node - the angle between the X direction of the coordinate system and the point where the orbit crosses the X-Y plane in the +Z direction.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateKeplerianSMA
member.summary: Semimajor Axis - half the length of the major (longest) axis of the orbital ellipse.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateKeplerianTA
member.summary: True Anomaly - the angle from the periapsis of the orbit to the spacecraft's position vector, measured in the direction of spacecraft motion.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateKeplerianW
member.summary: Argument of Periapsis - the angle measured in the direction of spacecraft motion, in the orbit plane, from the ascending node to the periapsis of the orbit.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateRadiationPressureArea
member.summary: Radiation Pressure (Albedo/Thermal) Area - the cross-sectional area of the spacecraft assumed perpendicular to the direction of central body radiation, used for central body radiation (albedo / thermal pressure) calculations.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateCk
member.summary: Radiation Pressure (Albedo/Thermal) Coefficient (Ck) - the reflectivity of the spacecraft used for central body radiation pressure (albedo / thermal pressure) calculations, where 2.0 is fully reflective and 1.0 is not reflective at all.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateSphericalAz
member.summary: Velocity Azimuth - the angle in the spacecraft local horizontal plane between the projection of the velocity vector onto that plane and the local +Z direction measured as positive in the clockwise direction from north.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateSphericalDec
member.summary: Declination - the angle from the X-Y plane of the coordinate system to the spacecraft position vector.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateSphericalHorizFPA
member.summary: Horizontal Flight Path Angle - the complement of the angle between the spacecraft velocity vector and the radius vector (90 deg minus the vertical flight path angle).

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateSphericalRA
member.summary: Right Ascension - angle measured in the inertial equatorial plane from the inertial X axis in a right-handed sense about the inertial Z axis to the spacecraft position vector.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateSphericalRMag
member.summary: Radius Magnitude - the magnitude of the spacecraft position vector.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateSphericalVMag
member.summary: Velocity Magnitude - the magnitude of the spacecraft velocity vector.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateSRPArea
member.summary: Solar Radiation Pressure (Spherical) Area - the cross-sectional area of the spacecraft assumed perpendicular to the direction of solar radiation, used for solar radiation calculations.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateTankPressure
member.summary: Tank Pressure - the fuel tank pressure.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateTankTemp
member.summary: Tank Temperature - the temperature of the fuel tank.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateTargetVecInAsympDec
member.summary: Declination of Incoming Asymptote - the declination of the incoming asymptote in the selected coordinate system.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateTargetVecInAsympRA
member.summary: Right Ascension of Incoming Asymptote - the right ascension of the hyperbolic incoming asymptote in the selected coordinate system.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateTargetVecInVelAzAtPeriapsis
member.summary: Velocity Azimuth at Periapsis - the inertial flight path azimuth of the trajectory measured at periapsis.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateTargetVecInC3
member.summary: C3 Energy - the energy of the orbit, computed as - mu / a, where mu is the gravity constant of the central body and a is the semimajor axis.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateTargetVecInRadOfPeriapsis
member.summary: Radius of Periapsis - distance from the center of mass of the central body to the periapsis of the hyperbolic orbit.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateTargetVecInTrueAnomaly
member.summary: True Anomaly - the angle from the periapsis of the orbit to the spacecraft's position vector, measured in the direction of spacecraft motion.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateTargetVecOutAsympDec
member.summary: Declination of Outgoing Asymptote - the declination of the outgoing asymptote in the selected coordinate system.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateTargetVecOutAsympRA
member.summary: Right Ascension of Outgoing Asymptote - the right ascension of the hyperbolic outgoing asymptote in the selected coordinate system.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateTargetVecOutVelAzAtPeriapsis
member.summary: Velocity Azimuth at Periapsis - the inertial flight path azimuth of the trajectory measured at periapsis.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateTargetVecOutC3
member.summary: C3 Energy - the energy of the orbit, computed as - mu / a, where mu is the gravity constant of the central body and a is the semimajor axis.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateTargetVecOutRadOfPeriapsis
member.summary: Radius of Periapsis - distance from the center of mass of the central body to the periapsis of the hyperbolic orbit.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateTargetVecOutTrueAnomaly
member.summary: True Anomaly - the angle from the periapsis of the orbit to the spacecraft's position vector, measured in the direction of spacecraft motion.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateMaxFuelMass
member.summary: Maximum Fuel Mass - the maximum fuel mass of the spacecraft; this parameter specifically applies to Finite Maneuver segments that are being executed in Backward Sequences.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateTankVolume
member.summary: Tank Volume - the volume of the fuel tank.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateDelaunayG

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateDelaunayH
member.summary: H - Z component of orbital angular momentum, G cos(inc).

member.summary: Inclination - The angle between the angular momentum vector (perpendicular to the plane of the orbit) and the inertial Z axis.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateDelaunayL

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateDelaunayMeanAnomaly

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateDelaunayRAAN
member.summary: Right Ascension of Ascending Node - The angle from the inertial X axis to the ascending node measured in a right-handed sense about the inertial Z axis in the equatorial plane.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateDelaunaySemiLatusRectum
member.summary: Semi-latus Rectum - Distance from focus to orbit at true anomaly of 90 degrees

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateDelaunaySMA
member.summary: Semimajor Axis - Half the length of the major (longest) axis of the orbital ellipse.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateDelaunayW
member.summary: Argument of Periapsis - The angle from the ascending node to the eccentricity vector measured in the direction of the satellite's motion and in the orbit plane.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateEquinoctialH
member.summary: H - With K, describe the shape and position of periapsis of the orbit, ecc * sin(RAAN + w)

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateEquinoctialK
member.summary: K - With H, describe the shape and position of periapsis of the orbit, ecc * cos(RAAN + w)

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateEquinoctialMeanLongitude
member.summary: Mean Longitude - RAAN + w + M

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateEquinoctialMeanMotion
member.summary: Mean Motion - The number of orbits per day (86400 sec/period), based on assumed two-body motion.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateEquinoctialP
member.summary: P - With Q, describes the orientation of the orbit plane, tan(inc/2) * sin(RAAN)

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateEquinoctialQ
member.summary: Q - With P, describes the orientation of the orbit plane, tan(inc/2) * cos(RAAN)

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateEquinoctialSMA
member.summary: Semimajor Axis - Half the length of the major (longest) axis of the orbital ellipse.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateMixedSphericalAltitude
member.summary: Altitude - The object's position above or below the reference ellipsoid. Altitude is measured along a normal to the surface of the reference ellipsoid.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateMixedSphericalAzimuth
member.summary: Azimuth - The angle in the satellite local horizontal plane between the projection of the inertial velocity vector onto this plane and the local north direction measured as positive in the clockwise direction.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateMixedSphericalHorizFPA
member.summary: Horizontal Flight Path Angle - The complement of the angle between the inertial velocity vector and the radius vector.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateMixedSphericalLatitude
member.summary: Latitude - The geodetic latitude of a point is the angle between the normal to the reference ellipsoid that passes through the satellite position and the equatorial plane.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateMixedSphericalLongitude
member.summary: Longitude

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateMixedSphericalVerticalFPA
member.summary: Vertical Flight Path Angle - The angle between the inertial velocity vector and the radius vector.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateMixedSphericalVMag
member.summary: Velocity Magnitude - The magnitude of the inertial velocity vector.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateSphericalVerticalFPA
member.summary: Vertical Flight Path Angle - The angle between the inertial velocity vector and the radius vector.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateKeplerianApoapsisAltShape
member.summary: Apoapsis Altitude - Shape Parameter - Distance from the surface of the central body to the point of maximum radius in the orbit.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateKeplerianApoapsisAltSize
member.summary: Apoapsis Altitude - Size Parameter - Distance from the surface of the central body to the point of maximum radius in the orbit.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateKeplerianApoapsisRadShape
member.summary: Apoapsis Radius - Shape Parameter - Distance from the center of the central body to the point of maximum radius in the orbit.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateKeplerianApoapsisRadSize
member.summary: Apoapsis Radius - Size Parameter - Distance from the center of the central body to the point of maximum radius in the orbit.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateKeplerianArgLat
member.summary: Argument of Latitude - The sum of the True Anomaly and the Argument of Perigee.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateKeplerianEccAnomaly
member.summary: Eccentric Anomaly - Angle measured with an origin at the center of the ellipse from the direction of perigee to a point on a circumscribing circle from which a line perpendicular to the SMA intersects the position of the satellite on the ellipse.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateKeplerianLAN
member.summary: Longitude of Ascending Node - Longitude of the Ascending Node is the Earth-fixed longitude where the satellite has crossed the inertial equator from south to north based on an assumption of two-body motion.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateKeplerianMeanAnomaly
member.summary: Mean Anomaly - The angle from the eccentricity vector to a position vector where the satellite would be if it were always moving at its average angular rate.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateKeplerianMeanMotion
member.summary: Mean Motion - The number of orbits per day (86400 sec/period), based on assumed two-body motion.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateKeplerianPeriapsisAltShape
member.summary: Periapsis Altitude - Shape Parameter - Distance from the surface of the central body to the point of minimum radius in the orbit.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateKeplerianPeriapsisAltSize
member.summary: Periapsis Altitude - Size Parameter - Distance from the surface of the central body to the point of minimum radius in the orbit.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateKeplerianPeriapsisRadShape
member.summary: Periapsis Radius - Shape Parameter - Distance from the center of the central body to the point of minimum radius in the orbit.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateKeplerianPeriapsisRadSize
member.summary: Periapsis Radius - Size Parameter - Distance from the surface of the central body to the point of minimum radius in the orbit.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateKeplerianPeriod
member.summary: Period - The duration of one orbit, based on assumed two-body motion.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlInitState.eVAControlInitStateKeplerianTimePastAN
member.summary: Time Past Ascending Node - The elapsed time since the last ascending node crossing based on assumed two-body motion.

member.name: T:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAFollowJoin
member.summary: Joining options for the Follow segment.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAFollowJoin.eVAFollowJoinSpecify
member.summary: Specify Joining Conditions - specify joining conditions to define when the spacecraft will begin to follow the leader. Joining conditions will become apparent on a new tab - Joining.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAFollowJoin.eVAFollowJoinAtBeginning
member.summary: Join at Beginning of Leader's Ephemeris - the spacecraft will follow the leader from the beginning of the leader's ephemeris.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAFollowJoin.eVAFollowJoinAtEnd
member.summary: Join at End of Leader's Ephemeris - the spacecraft will use the leader's final ephemeris point as the initial and final state of the Follow segment; the separation parameter will automatically be set to 'Separate at End of Leader's Ephemeris'.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAFollowJoin.eVAFollowJoinAtFinalEpochOfPreviousSeg
member.summary: Join at Final Epoch of Previous Segment - the spacecraft will follow the leader from the final epoch at the end of the previous segment.

member.name: T:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAFollowSeparation
member.summary: Separation options for the Follow segment.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAFollowSeparation.eVAFollowSeparationSpecify
member.summary: Specify Separation Conditions - specify separation conditions to define when the spacecraft will stop following the leader. Separation conditions will become apparent on a new tab - Separation.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAFollowSeparation.eVAFollowSeparationAtEndOfLeadersEphem
member.summary: Separate at End of Leader's Ephemeris - the spacecraft will follow the leader to the end of the leader's ephemeris and then separate.

member.name: T:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAFollowSpacecraftAndFuelTank
member.summary: Spacecraft parameter options for the Follow segment.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAFollowSpacecraftAndFuelTank.eVAFollowSpacecraftAndFuelTankSpecify
member.summary: Specify Spacecraft Configuration - manually define the spacecraft for this segment. Spacecraft physical parameters will become apparent on new tabs - Spacecraft Parameters and Fuel Tank.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAFollowSpacecraftAndFuelTank.eVAFollowSpacecraftAndFuelTankInherit
member.summary: Inherit Spacecraft Configuration From Previous Segment - the spacecraft will be defined by its configuration at the end of the previous segment. The configuration will not be changed by the Follow segment.

member.name: T:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlFollow
member.summary: Follow segment properties that can be selected as control parameters for a Target Sequence.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlFollow.eVAControlFollowFuelMass
member.summary: Fuel Mass - the mass of the spacecraft propellant. Enter a value in the selected mass unit (e.g. kg).

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlFollow.eVAControlFollowCd
member.summary: Drag Coefficient (Cd) - the dimensionless drag coefficient associated with the drag area.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlFollow.eVAControlFollowCr
member.summary: Solar Radiation Pressure (Spherical) Coefficient (Cr) - the reflectivity of the spacecraft used for solar radiation pressure calculations, where 2.0 is fully reflective and 1.0 is not reflective at all.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlFollow.eVAControlFollowDragArea
member.summary: Drag Area - the cross-sectional area of the spacecraft assumed perpendicular to the direction of motion, used for atmospheric drag calculations. Enter a value in the selected distance unit squared.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlFollow.eVAControlFollowDryMass
member.summary: Dry Mass - the mass of the spacecraft exclusive of propellant. Enter a value in the selected mass unit (e.g. kg).

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlFollow.eVAControlFollowFuelDensity
member.summary: Fuel Density - the density of the fuel tank. Enter a value in the selected mass unit per the selected distance unit cubed (e.g. kg/m^3).

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlFollow.eVAControlFollowK1
member.summary: GPS Solar Radiation Pressure K1 - if you are using a non-spherical SRP model, this field defines the model's K1 (scale) value.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlFollow.eVAControlFollowK2
member.summary: GPS Solar Radiation Pressure K2 - if you are using a non-spherical SRP model, this field defines the model's K2 (Y bias) value.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlFollow.eVAControlFollowRadiationPressureArea
member.summary: The cross-sectional area of the spacecraft assumed perpendicular to the direction of central body radiation, used for central body radiation (albedo / thermal pressure) calculations. Enter a value in the selected distance unit squared.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlFollow.eVAControlFollowCk
member.summary: Radiation Pressure (Albedo/Thermal) Coefficient (Ck) - the reflectivity of the spacecraft used for central body radiation pressure (albedo / thermal pressure) calculations, where 2.0 is fully reflective and 1.0 is not reflective at all.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlFollow.eVAControlFollowSRPArea
member.summary: Solar Radiation Pressure (Spherical) Area - the cross-sectional area of the spacecraft assumed perpendicular to the direction of solar radiation, used for solar radiation calculations. Enter a value in the selected distance unit squared.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlFollow.eVAControlFollowTankPressure
member.summary: Tank Pressure - the fuel tank pressure. Enter a value in the selected pressure unit (e.g. Pa).

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlFollow.eVAControlFollowTankTemp
member.summary: Tank Temperature - the temperature of the fuel tank. Enter a value in the selected temperature unit.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAControlFollow.eVAControlFollowMaxFuelMass
member.summary: Maximum Fuel Mass - the maximum fuel mass of the spacecraft; this parameter specifically applies to Finite Maneuver segments that are being executed in Backward Sequences. Enter a value in the selected mass unit (e.g. kg).

member.summary: Pressure-Regulated - constant pressure is maintained in the fuel tank through some pressurization mechanism as the propellant mass decreases.

member.summary: Thrust options.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAThrustType.eVAThrustTypeAffectsAccelAndMassFlow
member.summary: Affects Acceleration and Mass Flow Calculations - may represent an inefficiency in the propulsion tanks and feed lines.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAThrustType.eVAThrustTypeAffectsAccelOnly
member.summary: Affects Acceleration Only - an efficiency of 0.98 means that only 98% of the fuel will be spent to get 98% thrust. For example, a thrust efficiency affecting acceleration only may represent some problem in the combustion chamber.

member.summary: This property is only available for use with a duration stopping condition. If selected, you are setting the maneuver to start half the time before the previous segment ended.

member.summary: The value by which to adjust the centering of the burn. A positive value will center the burn after the previous segment ends by the amount specified in the Burn Center Bias field. Uses Time Dimension.

member.summary: Override Maximum Propagation Time - if there is a duration or epoch stopping condition that occurs after the maximum propagation time, ignore the maximum propagation time.

member.summary: Solar Radiation Pressure (Spherical) Area - the cross-sectional area of the spacecraft assumed perpendicular to the direction of solar radiation, used for solar radiation calculations.

member.summary: Dry Mass - the mass of the spacecraft exclusive of propellant.

member.summary: The mass of the spacecraft propellant.

member.summary: The density of the fuel tank.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAUpdateParam.eVAUpdateParamTankPressure
member.summary: The fuel tank pressure.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAUpdateParam.eVAUpdateParamTankTemp
member.summary: The temperature of the fuel tank.

member.name: F:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgEVAUpdateParam.eVAUpdateParamCr
member.summary: Solar Radiation Pressure (Spherical) Coefficient (Cr) - the reflectivity of the spacecraft used for solar radiation pressure calculations, where 2.0 is fully reflective and 1.0 is not reflective at all.

member.summary: The MCS Options.

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgVAMCSOptions.DrawTrajectoryIn2D
member.summary: If true, Astrogator will draw the trajectory in the 2D Graphics windows as the ephemeris is calculated during the current run.

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgVAMCSOptions.DrawTrajectoryIn3D
member.summary: If true, Astrogator will draw the trajectory in the 3D Graphics windows as the ephemeris is calculated during the current run.

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgVAMCSOptions.UpdateAnimationTimeForAllObjects
member.summary: If true, all other objects will be animated so that they appear at the proper position for the time being computed as the trajectory is calculated.

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgVAMCSOptions.ClearDWCGraphicsBeforeEachRun
member.summary: If true, Astrogator will automatically clear all target iteration graphics of the previous run - in all graphics windows - before the current run draws new calculations.

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgVAMCSOptions.ClearAdditionalBPlanePoints
member.summary: If true, Astrogator will clear all additional B-Plane points from any previous run - in all graphics windows - before the current run.

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgVAMCSOptions.PropagateOnApply
member.summary: If true, Astrogator will propagate trajectories whenever you click OK or Apply on the Orbit page. If you want to close the Properties Browser for the satellite without running the MCS, make certain this option is disabled.

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgVAMCSOptions.EnableTrajectorySegmentColors
member.summary: If true, trajectory segments are displayed in the 2D Graphics window in the colors selected for the respective segments; otherwise the color of the trajectory is defined by the 2D Graphics Attributes page.

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgVAMCSOptions.SaveNumbersInRawFormat
member.summary: If true, Astrogator will store satellite information in binary format - to preserve the maximum amount of precision.

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgVAMCSOptions.StoppingConditionTimeTolerance
member.summary: The time tolerance, which will be applied with respect to desired trip values throughout the MCS. If this value is set to zero, time tolerance will not be applied.

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgVAMCSOptions.EnableSegmentControls
member.summary: If true, Astrogator will automatically add independent variables to differential correctors.

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgVAMCSOptions.EnableSegmentResults
member.summary: If true, Astrogator will automatically add dependent variables to differential correctors.

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgVAMCSOptions.EnableLogging
member.summary: If true, target sequences can be set to produce 'run history' log files for differential corrector profiles. By default, a target sequence does not produce a log file.

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgVAMCSOptions.GraphicsUpdateRate
member.summary: The rate (between 0 and 1) at which to update graphics. Dimensionless.

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgVAMCSOptions.PromoteControls
member.summary: If true, a target sequence will be able to affect controls and results within a nested target sequence in addition to its own.

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgVAMCSOptions.UseNominalSettings
member.summary: If true, components or segments that are modified by a target sequence will be restored to their nominal values as soon as the target sequence completes its run.

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgVAMCSOptions.MinEphemStep
member.summary: The minimum step size for saving ephemeris. Uses Time Dimension.

member.name: P:AGI.STKObjects.Astrogator.AgVAMCSOptions.GenerateEphemeris
